===============================================================================
1. Prerequisites:
===============================================================================

pytorch and torchvision is required to run the test app. To install pytorch and torchvision,
run following commands:

  $ pip3 install torch torchvision

for Ubuntu 24.04, use:

  $ pip3 install torch torchvision --break-system-packages

===============================================================================
2. Purpose:
===============================================================================

This document shall describe about the sample deepstream_test1 application.

It is meant for demonstration of how to use the various DeepStream SDK
elements in the pipeline and extract meaningful insights from a video stream using the service-maker API.

===============================================================================
3. Usage:
===============================================================================

  Run with the h264 elementary stream or YAML pipeline config file.
   With YAML Pipeline config approach, user can modify the config file to configure
   pipeline properties.

    $ python3 deepstream_test1.py <h264_elementary_stream>

    Or

    $ python3 deepstream_test1.py <pipeline config in yaml>